CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper November 6, 1948, pg. 13, reads: "Combination Session - These ministers and members of the local NAACP board of directors were feted at a banquet held in Central Baptist Church last week. Shown seated at the table starting in the rear from right to left: The Rev. D. H. Thomas, Roland Sawyer, Mrs. Daisy Lampkin, Mrs. Sue Corsey, The Rev. J. C. Hairston, the Rev. Porter Phillips, the Rev. S. D. Rudder, the Rev. John Washington, the Rev. Eugene Roberts, the Rev. S. L. Spear, William H. Richardson, Atty. Paul Jones, the Rev. S. S. Thurston, the Rev. A. H. Durham, Mrs. Addie Gupton, the Rev. C. A. Burrell, Mrs. Jeanne Scott, the Rev. C. E. Queen, James A. Jordon and John G. Jones. -  Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Ministers and members of Pittsburgh chapter NAACP at banquet, including Rev. D. H. Thomas, Roland Sawyer, Daisy Lampkin, Sue Corsey, Rev. J. C. Hairston, Rev. Porter Phillips, Rev. S. D. Rudder, Rev. John Washington, Rev. Eugene Roberts, Rev. S. L. Spear, William H. Richardson, Atty. Paul Jones, Rev. S. S. Thurston, Rev. A. H. Durham, Addie Gupton, Rev. C. A. Burrell, Jeanne Scott, Rev. C. E. Queen, James A. Jordon, and John G. Jones in Central Baptist Church
